\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
The area of the dart board is 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$
\backslash
pi r^2$
\end_layout

\end_inset

 and so the probability of hitting the board at all is 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$
\backslash
pi r^2/A$
\end_layout

\end_inset

 and so the probability of missing the board is then 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$P(
\backslash
text{scoring }0
\backslash
text{ points})=1-
\backslash
pi r^2/A$
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 The rest of the values for the probability mass function are the same as
 they are in 
\series bold

\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

Ex 1.2.7 
\series default
except renormalized by 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$A$
\end_layout

\end_inset

 instead of by the area of the dartboard, i.e.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$$P(
\backslash
text{scoring }i
\backslash
text{ points}) = 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
left
\backslash
{ 	
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

		
\backslash
begin{array}{ll} 		
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

				 1-
\backslash
pi r^2/A & 
\backslash
mbox{if } i = 0 
\backslash

\backslash

\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

				 
\backslash
frac{
\backslash
pi r^2}{A}
\backslash
frac{(6-i)^2 -(5-i)^2}{5^2} & 
\backslash
mbox{if } i = 1,2,3,4,5 	
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

		
\backslash
end{array} 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
right.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$$
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$P(
\backslash
